1. Dam_name—The official name of the dam or impoundment. No abbreviations used unless a part of the official name. Popular name used when the dam does not have official name (1).
2. Other_dam_name—Previous name of the dam. Name which is used commonly other than the official name (1).
3. State—State in which the dam and reservoir are located according to the NID (1).
4. NIDID—Unique identification number issued by the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers. Formerly known as the National ID (1).
5. Year_Completed— Year construction was completed on dam (1).
6. Reservoir_Age— The year 2015 minus the year construction was completed.
7. Hydraulic_Height (feet)—The vertical difference between the maximum design water level and the lowest point in the original streambed (1).
8. NID_Height (feet)—A calculated value based on dam height, structural height, and hydraulic height that provides a single value to facilitate database queries (1).
9. Maximum_Discharge (cubic feet/second)—Maximum discharge from the reservoir that the spillway can accommodate (1).
10. Maximum_Storage (acre-feet)—The total storage space in a reservoir below the maximum attainable water surface elevation (1).
11. Normal_Storage (acre-feet)—The total storage space in a reservoir below the normal retention level, including dead and inactive storage and excluding any flood control or surface storage (1).
12. NID_Storage (acre-feet)—Volume calculated by the NID based on the maximum storage and normal storage that provides a single storage value to facilitate database queries (1).
13. NID_Storage (cubic feet)—Volume calculated by the NID based on the maximum storage and normal storage that provides a single storage value multiplied by 43,560 (1).
14. Surface_Area (acres)—The number of acres covered by the surface of the reservoir at its normal retention level (1).
15. Surface_Area (square feet)—The number of acres covered by the surface of the reservoir at its normal retention level multiplied by 43,560 (8).
16. Surface_Area (square miles)—The number of acres covered by the surface of the reservoir at its normal retention level, which is equal to acre—feet multiplied by 0.0015625 (8).
17. Surface_Area (square meters)—The number of acres covered by the surface of the reservoir at its normal retention level multiplied by 4046.86 (8).
18. Surface_Area (square kilometers)—The number of acres covered by the surface of the reservoir at its normal retention level multiplied by 0.00404686 (8).
19. Drainage_Area (square miles)—The area of land where all the water which drains from it or beneath it collects in the same place (1).
20. Drainage_Area (square kilometers)—The area of land where all the water which drains from it or beneath it collects in the same place (8).
21. Drainage_Area (acres)—The area of land where all the water which drains from it or beneath it collects in the same place (8).
22. Drainage_Area (square feet)—The area of land where all the water which drains from it or beneath it collects in the same place (8).
23. Reservoir_Perimeter (feet)—Length of the reservoir shoreline calculated in ArcGIS from National Hydrography Dataset digitized from USGS Topographic Maps (4).
24. Reservoir_Perimeter (kilometer)—Length of the reservoir shoreline calculated in ArcGIS from National Hydrography Dataset digitized from USGS Topographic Maps (8).
25. Reservoir_Perimeter (miles)—Length of the reservoir shoreline calculated in ArcGIS from National Hydrography Dataset digitized from USGS Topographic Maps (8).

26. Shoreline_Development_Index—Unitless number calculated by dividing the shoreline distance by the perimeter of a circle of the same area as the lake. (DL) = SL / 2*√ (π*A0) where SL is the reservoir perimeter and A0 is the area of the lake (2).
28. Mean_Depth (Zmean)—Volume divided by the surface area. Zmean = V/A0 where V is the volume of the reservoir at normal storage and A0 is the area of the reservoir (2).

30. Index_of_Basin_Permanence (IBP)—A morphometric index that is a reflection of the littoral effect on basin volume. IBP = V/SL where V is the volume of the reservoir at normal storage and SL is the length of the reservoir perimeter (11).

32. Development_of_Volume (Dv)—A measure of the departure of the shape of the lake basin from that of a cone. (Dv)= 3*Zmean/Zmax where Zmean is the mean depth of the reservoir and Zmax is the maximum depth of the reservoir as hydraulic height (2).
36. Mean_Depth_Maximum_Depth_Ratio (Depth Ratio)—As depth ratio decreases, potential nutrient recycling from the sediment surface, productivity, and sediment accretion rate increases (6).
38. Mean_Q (cubic feet/second)—Average amount of water passing a given point per unit of time (7).
40. Catchment_Area_Surface_Area_Ratio—Calculated as drainage area divided by surface area of the reservoir (10).
42. Relative_Depth (Zr)—The maximum depth as a percentage of mean diameter. Zr = 50 * Zmax * √ (π)*(√(A0) (3).
44. Surface_Area_Lake_Volume_Ratio—Calculated as surface area divided by the reservoir volume at normal storage (9).
52. AreaSqKm—Area of an areal feature based on Albers Equal Area conic (4).
54. Elevation (meters)—Vertical distance from a given datum (4).
56. GNIS_Name—U.S. Board on Geographic Names Identification System feature name by which a particular geographic feature is known (4).

58. ReachCode—Unique identifier for a 'reach'. The first eight numbers are the WBD_HUC8. The next six numbers are randomly assigned, sequential numbers that are unique within a HUC 14-character value (4).
60. E2RF1 —A secondary unique reach identification number that reflects revisions in process steps (5).
62. HUC—Hydrologic Cataloging unit of the reach (5).
64. MEANV(feet per second)—Velocity corresponding to mean streamflow for reach (5).
66. STRAHLER—Strahler stream order of the reach (5).
68. RR—"River Reach" identifier. An 11-digit identification number consisting of an 8-digit hydrologic unit code and 3-digit reach segment number (5).
